<item>
            <title>[FLINK-3005] Commons-collections object deserialization remote command execution vulnerability</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3005</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://foxglovesecurity.com/2015/11/06/what-do-weblogic-websphere-jboss-jenkins-opennms-and-your-application-have-in-common-this-vulnerability/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://foxglovesecurity.com/2015/11/06/what-do-weblogic-websphere-jboss-jenkins-opennms-and-your-application-have-in-common-this-vulnerability/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TL;DR: If you have commons-collections on your classpath and accept and process Java object serialization data, then you may have an exploitable remote command execution vulnerability.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Brief search in code base for ObjectInputStream reveals several places where the vulnerability exists.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
